<h3 id="what-is-dynamic-programming">What is Dynamic Programming?</h3>
<p>Dynamic Programming (DP) is often considered one of the most challenging topics in computer science algorithms. However, at its core, it is simply <strong>an optimization technique</strong>.</p>
<p>The fundamental idea of DP is <strong>&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t Repeat Yourself.&rdquo;</strong></p>
<p>If you have already solved a sub-problem, you should save the result (cache it) so that you never have to calculate it again. By trading a little bit of <strong>space</strong> (to store results) for <strong>time</strong> (to avoid re-calculation), DP can turn an inefficient exponential algorithm ($O(2^n)$) into a highly efficient linear one ($O(n)$).</p>]]></description></item><item><title>[Spring] 2. Analysis of Custom Thread Pools and Thread Reuse in Spring Async Interfaces</title><link>https://gooddayday.github.io/en/2025/10/spring-2.-spring-async-threadpool-and-thread-reuse/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Oct 2025 10:23:17 +0800</pubDate><author>GoodyHao</author><guid>https://gooddayday.github.io/en/2025/10/spring-2.-spring-async-threadpool-and-thread-reuse/</guid><description><![CDATA[<h2 id="preface">Preface</h2>
